Ratargul Swamp Forest, often heralded as the 'Amazon of Bangladesh,' is a freshwater swamp forest in Sylhet District, Bangladesh, known for its unique ecosystem and biodiversity. It is a popular eco-tourism destination.

Miracle Garden indeed! World's largest natural flower garden - home to at least 50 million flowers of different varieties! Located right next to the existing Dubai Miracle Garden, there's Dubai Butterfly Garden featuring 15,000 butterflies of around 50 varieties of butterfly in different sizes and colors flying around the visitors in the open.
